6.  Apply the helper lemma `helper` to each term `eLpNorm (T gᵢ) 1 (ν.restrict G)`. The `gcongr` tactic can do this. We need to provide the hypotheses `hf'` (which states `gᵢ` is `memLorentz`) and `measurable_G` and `G_finite` (which are in the context). `hf.1` gives the `aestronglyMeasurable` property.
    ```tactics
    gcongr
    all_goals
      try { apply helper (hf.1) _ _ _ }
      all_goals
        try { tauto }
        all_goals
          try { aesop }
    ```
    This will transform the goal into:
    `⊢ (c / p) * eLorentzNorm g₁ p 1 μ * ν G ^ p'⁻¹.toReal + (c / p) * eLorentzNorm g₂ p 1 μ * ν G ^ p'⁻¹.toReal + (c / p) * eLorentzNorm g₃ p 1 μ * ν G ^ p'⁻¹.toReal + (c / p) * eLorentzNorm g₄ p 1 μ * ν G ^ p'⁻¹.toReal ≤ (c / p) * eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ * ν G ^ p'⁻¹.toReal`

